Scenario: shop-msg send by --bc <name> succeeds when the registered BC's shop_root path does not exist on the lead host
  Given "shopsystem-messaging" is registered in the messaging registry as a BC whose shop_root column points to a filesystem path that does not exist on the lead host
  And no other registry mutation is required for the lead's own entry to be present
  When I run shop-msg send assign_scenarios --bc shopsystem-messaging with a valid payload and work-id "reg-mxxm-101"
  Then the command exits zero
  And stderr contains no "registry entry for ... points to path ... which does not exist on disk" warning
  And stderr contains no "registry may be stale" warning
  And shop-msg pending inbox --bc shopsystem-messaging includes work-id "reg-mxxm-101"
